  "riddle": "1. Seek the center of modern healthcare in the city where waterways weave through bustling streets — what is its home country and capital?\n\n2. What height does this vibrant metropolis rise above sea level, measured in meters?\n\n3. Within the city mentioned, which letter begins its name? Discover its position in the alphabet.\n\n4. A grand structure commemorates a transition; what year marked its groundbreaking ceremony?\n\n5. Where does the sacred fig tree reside, famous for its age and spiritual significance?\n\n6. In what location do devotees gather for a water-cutting ceremony that celebrates renewal?\n\n7. How high does the Mahaweli River flow through Getambe, Kandy, above sea level?\n\n8. What score do visitors bestow upon this celebrated river, reflecting their delight?\n\n9. Combine the river's elevation with the rating you discovered — what new number emerges?\n\n10. Once more, what accolade do travelers give to the Mahaweli River in Getambe, Kandy?\n\n11. Find the first letter of the answer from clue 6, and determine its position in the alphabet.\n\n12. Where does a pivotal site in spiritual journeys lie, as indicated by coordinates found on its page?\n\n13. Seek a pilgrimage path that encircles a sacred site; what place stands at its heart?\n\n14. What elevation does the sacred circuit around Kurukshetra reach?\n\n15. What rating do pilgrims assign to this revered pilgrimage route?\n\n16. Bring together the elevation from clue 14 and the rating from clue 15 — what result do you find?\n\n17. In the dish associated with the answer from clue 13, what preparation method is described for its main ingredient?\n\n18. Take the sum of the findings from clue 3 and clue 9, then compute: what is the result when you take that sum and apply modulo 10? Recall the formula: (the position from clue 3 + the sum from clue 9) % 10.",
